<plot>When the ferocious giant Golimyr threatens the peaceful village of the Zites, King Sullic sends a proclamation throughout the land calling for a champion to vanquish the foe. To the King's dismay, the only champion who rises to their aid is young Davie, a peaceful pear grower whose only defense is a sling, a sheep and his faith. Set within the imaginative fantasy and world of renowned artist James C. Chritensen and based on the biblical story of David and Goliath, this stop-motion animated adventure is bursting with visual wonders. From sneeze-powered windmills to a colossal ship made of stone, join Davie and his woolly sidekick Chops as they discover a little Faith can do Giant things.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?130409</url></doc>
